DATA CLOUD
About Salesforce Data Cloud

Ingest, harmonize, unify, and analyze streaming and batch data with Salesforce Data Cloud. Then use that data to unlock meaningful and intelligent experiences across Customer 360 applications and beyond.

How Does It Work?
Connect all your data sources whether batch or streaming data.
Prepare your data through transformation and data governance features.
Harmonize your data to a standard data model.
Unify data with identity resolution rulesets.
Query and analyze data using insights.
Use AI to predict behavior.
Segment your data and activate to use in various channels to create personalized experiences.
Analyze your data using supported analytic tools.
Output data to multiple sources to act on data based on your business needs.
Continue to review, measure, and optimize data.

Data Cloud is for all users and offers functionality across roles.

USER	DESCRIPTION	LEARN MORE
Admins	Grow your admin career with Data Cloud.	Trailhead: Administer Data Cloud
Analysts	Expand the capabilities of Data Cloud using Tableau.	Tableau: Tableau Cloud Help Documentation
Builders	Build applications and features using Data Cloud.	ISVforce Guide: Use Managed Packages to Develop Your AppExchange Solution
Business Users	Ingest data into Data Cloud for a variety of use cases, regardless of role or industry.	Salesforce Help: Build a Data Cloud with Salesforce
Data Architects	Map and model data for your company.	Salesforce Architects: Diagram Frameworks
Developers	Use APIs and SDKs to interact with Data Cloud.	Salesforce Developers: Data Cloud Developer Center
Marketers	Segment audiences to create cross-channel campaigns to reach your customers.	Trailhead: Segmentation in Data Cloud
Partners	Implement Data Cloud for your customers.	Salesforce Partners: Partner Learning Camp
Customize Your Data Cloud Experience

Data Cloud is built to scale, allowing you to bundle features as needed. Some Data Cloud features are offered as add-on licenses, and others have usage limitations, though many limits can be adjusted to meet your business needs. Learn about current Data Cloud Limits and Guidelines and then work with your account executive to find a solution that meets your goals.

Data Cloud Starter

You have the base functionality and features of Data Cloud.

Start planning for Data Cloud: Get Started Using Data Cloud
Learn more about data usage that impact pricing: Data Usage in Data Cloud
Add user permissions to your users: User Roles and Permission Sets in Data Cloud
Data Cloud with Tableau

You have all the functionality of Data Cloud, along with the power of robust analytics with Tableau Enterprise.

Learn about Data Cloud and Tableau in Unlock Hidden Insights with Tableau.
Marketing Use Cases for Data Cloud

You have all the functionality of Data Cloud and with the addition of Segmentation and Activation, you can create meaningful audience segments and use those segments to create personalized customer communications and journeys.

After you have your data ingested and unified, get started building segments: Create and Activate Segments
Industry Use Cases for Data Cloud

Use the power of Data Cloud to solve various business needs with our industry-specific solutions.

Connect and integrate client data to give financial institutions a unified view of their client. Learn more about Data Cloud for Financial Services Cloud.
Aggregate health data and calculate scores for Unified Health Scoring in Health Cloud. Learn more about connecting Data Cloud and Health Cloud: Integrate Data Cloud with Unified Health Scoring
Data Cloud Glossary of Terms
Learn the definition of terms associated with Data Cloud.
Data Cloud Changes
Stay up to date with Data Cloud feature releases. Features are released up to twice a month. See the current release notes for changes made during a Salesforce three-times-a-year release.
Data Cloud Resources
In addition to help content, find links to videos, Trailhead, and Trailblazer content available to help learn Data Cloud.
Data Cloud and Cross-Cloud Implementation Guides
Use printable PDF guides to set up, administer, and configure Data Cloud features and applications. PDF guides are updated regularly, so check the date of any downloaded and saved guides before beginning your implementation.
Data Cloud Cross-Product Solutions
Review various cross-product use cases and solutions for Data Cloud.
